deck: Roving thug in the Daughters of the Amazons.
description:
Origin

Member of the militaristic order the Daughters of the Amazon.

Creation

Written by Brian K. Vaughan and drawn by Pia Guerra.

Major Story Arcs

Chloe leads a small group of the Daughters of the Amazon to the Washington Monument and begins defacing it. Yorick shows up to defend his side of the species and Chloe leads the women into beating up Yorick. Chloe is sprayed in the face with red spray paint before the women get the upper-hand. She nearly kills Yorick but is stopped by Agent 355. She is then knocked out by Agent 355. She stays down and overhears that Yorick and Agent 355 are headed for Boston. She runs to her leader, Victoria, and alerts her that a man is headed to Boston.
name: Chloe

deck: Musician and mourner of the dead great bands.
description:
Origin

Bleeding-heart musician that traveled the world to pay homage to fallen rock stars.

Creation

Written by Brian K. Vaughan and drawn by Pia Guerra.

Major Story Arcs

Unbeknownst to Rose, Yorick joins her at the Washington Memorial and the two mourn the passing of the great rock bands. Rose expresses her intent to head to the United Kingdom to join with a musicians commune but is cut short when the Daughters of the Amazon show up and begin wrecking the scene. Rose supposedly flees when Yorick goes to confront the gang.
name: Rose

deck: A "war veteran" robot that had previously killed off the entire human race, later served as an abused office drone. After saving 34RTH from an alien invasion, he became a general in the army.
description:
Current Events

D4VE lives on 34RTH as an office drone (quite literally). His son that he ordered months ago has finally arrived, and a new species of aliens have also arrived on the planet.

Creation

D4VE was created by writer Ryan Ferrier and artist Valentin Ramon for his title D4VE, published by monkeybrain Comics in 2013.

Origin

D4VE's origin is unknown as of yet, but it is heavily inferred that he was, like the other thousands of robots, created by humans to serve a certain task. However, the robots became advanced enough to form their own conscious thoughts, revolted, and killed off the entire human race. It was shown that D4VE was one of the robots that served in combat and also helped fight off numerous alien races. After the wars robots seemed to act entirely like humans, adopting their culture and way of life. D4VE has a wife 54LLY (whom he later divorced) and a son 5COTTY. However, he is now a "nobody" working as an office drone.

Powers and Abilities

Durable exo-skeleton - It is assumed from his robot form that he cannot experience pain and has an ultra-durable alloy which prevents him from harm.

Enhanced strength - D4VE was seen day-dreaming about a possible past experience in which he punched an alien right through a building wall.

Weapon experience - Seen in the flashbacks, D4VE was shown to have taken down numerous alien opponents armed with a shotgun of sorts.
name: D4VE
